After the speech, I was given some feedback from a fellow Toastmaster, Steve, on
things that I did well and things that I could improve on in the future. Even
though this was now almost a year and a half ago, I clearly remember learning
new things from his perspective on the speech. The first was that he noticed
that there were oohs and laughing coming from the audience. I was so tensed up
and nervous that I never even noticed the reaction that was coming from the
audience. He also mentioned that I repeated the word sour frequently throughout
the speech. I noticed this after watching through my recording. I use the word
sour 14 times. One salient point that he made was that my eye contact was
missing from a large portion of the speech.

