Later that evening at a club social event at Tied House, I got feedback some of
the members there. One suggestion that I should have have brought the entire
device in to show off how coffee was actually made in it. It was a bit weird
just having the bottom piece of the device. Through the feedback in the notes, I
was told that the ending could have been more impactful with more of a message.

With all of this feedback in my hands, I sat on it for a few months. When I came
back to it again, I rewrote the speech in some signficant changes.

- I decided to write and memorize my opening and conclusions. There were the
  weakest points of my speech (in my opinion).
- I made sure to actually bring my AeroPress to the next speech. It was weird
  that I didn't bring it in when I thought about it. I planned the demonstration
  as the point where I would try to address feedback about eye contact
  deliberately.
- I practiced. A lot more than I did the first time around. When I watched my
  second speech, I looked a lot more rehearsed. I remember recording myself
  quite a bit this time through.

