These two speeches, though only a few months apart, feel leagues apart in terms
of the quality of the speech. I think the feedback significantly influenced how
I approached the speech this time around. The practice also smoothed the
delivery. And, though not in my control, the camera angle was a bit better. It's
actually very difficult for me to sit through the first rendition of the speech,
but much easier to watch the second one several times over.

I attribute my improvement to great feedback from the entire club, and the
process of going back and improving of the speech that I gave. With every speech
comes some new aspect that you can improve on.
